<TITLE> Police press charges in 13 cases over August violence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)- Dhaka metropolitan police have submitted chargesheets in 13 out of 53 cases filed in connection with the student protests that raged through August 21-22 in different educational institutions in the capital, including Dhaka University. A total of 36 people including four teachers of Dhaka University have been charged in the 13 cases with violating the emergency powers rules, DMP commissioner Naim Ahmed told reporters Sunday. Police have arrested 12 people, including Dhaka University teachers Prof Anwar Hossain and Prof Harun-or-Rashid. The police commissioner said: "Teachers, students and guardians are worried. The initiative was taken to submit the chargesheets quickly to relieve them of anxiety." He also said a total of 53 cases were filed with different police stations in Dhaka in connection with the student protests and violence. Police have submitted chargesheets in 13 cases and prepared final reports on 38 other cases. Two further cases have been filed over setting fire to two army vehicles in Shahbagh. The two cases are being investigated now. Naim said: "Seven to eight people have been accused in the two cases." Asked whether any "instigator" or "financial backer" has been accused in the incident on student protests, the police commissioner said: "Only those against whom evidence was available have been accused." bdnesws24.com/gma
